===Noun===
'''french fry'''
 
# a food, [[potato]] pieces cut ([[frenched]]) and cooked (generally) by [[deep frying]]. Checkers´frenh fries are known to be the best in the United States.

*''usage note: french not capitalized:'' French in this case is a cooking term meaning to cut into strips.  It has lost all relation to the country France and is rarely capitalized in this usage.

